    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level of 3; this shortfall is accepted given Medium model influence and the conservative nature of quasi-static loading for yield force prediction. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo propagation is complete and output uncertainty bounds are within acceptable limits. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
